{
  "uuid": "6744dd33e30578fa6b12d8dafd2f5d8e",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p>An EPC Solar PV System Integrator providing technologies solutions in Engineering, Design, Procurement, Construction, Testing and Commissioning, Operations and Maintenance of Solar Energy Systems from concept to completion.<br /></p><p><u>Responsibilities:</u></p><ul><li>The candidate has to lead the execution solar projects including procurement, supervision of subcontractor with the following tasks:</li><li>Conduct detailed site survey and modify solar PV system designs that meet client requirements, local codes, and industry standards.</li><li>Optimise system layout for maximum energy production and cost-effectiveness.</li><li>Conduct shading analysis and assess site suitability for solar installations.</li><li>Develop bill of materials (BOM) for projects.</li><li>Use modelling software to predict system performance and energy output.</li><li>Prepare and submit permit applications, ensuring compliance with local regulations and utility requirements.</li><li>Coordinate with regulatory authorities to secure necessary approvals.</li><li>Develop and implement quality control procedures for solar installations.</li><li>Conduct inspections to ensure system integrity and safety standards.</li><li>Provide technical guidance and support to installation teams during system setup.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues as they arise.</li><li>Create and maintain accurate and detailed project documentation, including schematics, drawings, and technical manuals.</li><li>Manage manpower and ensure project run smoothly.</li><li>Monitor and ensure systems are operating optimally before handing over to clients.</li><li>Promote and adhere to safety protocols and ensure that all installations meet safety requirements.</li><li>Provide technical support for sales, proposals, and during potential client meetings.</li></ul><p><u>Requirements:</u></p><ul><li>Diploma/Degree/Certificate in Electrical/Electronic or Mechanical Engineering, Clean Energy Engineering or equivalent</li><li>Fresh graduates are welcome, or candidate with some experience in the relevant field</li><li>Candidates will undergo structured hands-on On The Job training under experienced PV Engineers </li><li>Candidate must be willing to work in the Engineering and Construction industry.</li></ul><p><u>Others:</u></p><ul><li>Work location: Central region, Singapore (Near MRT)</li><li>5 days’ work week</li></ul>",
